Estimated limit curve for the dimension normalized curvature measures

mu returns a pre-computed table and lookup functions for the estimated limit curve for dimension normalized curvature measures (see accompanying vignette for definition; we use C=0.2).

mu()

Value

The output of mu is a list of three elements:

  • table: a table of function values

  • lkup_rho: a corresponding lookup function for rho in terms of kappa

  • lkup_kappa: a corresponding lookup function for kappa in terms of rho

See also

leigh, rate, pat_bnd

Package: symconivol

Examples

M <- mu()
ggplot(M$table, aes(x=rho,y=kappa)) + geom_line()
#> Error in ggplot(M$table, aes(x = rho, y = kappa)): could not find function "ggplot"
rho <- (0:10)/10
matrix(c(rho, M$lkup_kappa(rho)),11,2)
